Covering new The Legend of Zelda Movie Teaser Trailer & First Look Breakdown and Easter Eggs. References to previous Zelda Video Games, Nintendo Next Movies, why The Legend of Zelda Movie is live action and not animated like the Super Mario Brothers Movie and Super Mario Galaxy Movie. 

A live-action adaptation of the video game franchise. 'The Legend of Zelda' follows Link, a young warrior destined to protect the magical kingdom of Hyrule from the forces of darkness. The land is under threat from Ganon, a ruthless warlord who seeks the Triforce-an ancient relic said to grant limitless power. To stop him, Link must embark on a perilous journey, battling monstrous creatures, exploring treacherous dungeons, and solving intricate puzzles to uncover sacred artifacts that can aid him in his quest.

This movie will adapt elements and characters from several different Zelda Games in the franchise, the same way the Super Mario Brothers Movies are doing. I'll do more videos for it as we get more teasers and trailers!

Lots more Marvel &DC Trailers coming at CCXP and soon. Avengers Doomsday Trailer, Avengers 6 Secret Wars Trailer. Spider-Man Brand New Day Trailer, Lanterns Trailer Green Lantern HBO & Supergirl Trailer!

Just about a month before you’re back in the Wasteland. Until then, please enjoy the official trailer for Fallout Season Two. Starring Ella Purnell, Aaron Moten, Walton Goggins, and more. Arriving December 17 only on Prime.
 
» Watch Fallout on Prime Video: https://amzn.to/3JrdwZH
» SUBSCRIBE: http://bit.ly/PrimeVideoSubscribe
 
About Fallout:
Based on one of the greatest video games of all time, Fallout is the story of haves and have-nots in a world in which there’s almost nothing left to have. 200 years after the apocalypse, the gentle denizens of luxury fallout shelters are forced to return to the incredibly complex, gleefully weird and highly violent universe waiting for them above.

About Prime Video:
Want to watch it now? We’ve got it. This week’s newest movies, last night’s TV shows, classic favorites, and more are available to stream instantly, plus all your videos are stored in Your Video Library. snippet.title: Toni Braxton - "He Wasn't Man Enough" Film (Trailer)
snippet.description:
#ToniBraxton #YvetteNicoleBrown #EssenceAtkins

The all-new original film, Toni Braxton’s He Wasn’t Man Enough, is inspired by Grammy® Award winner Toni Braxton’s best-selling hit of the same name and Braxton executive produces and stars alongside NAACP Image Award nominee Essence Attkins and Emmy® nominee Yvette Nicole Brown.

Set to premiere Saturday, November 22 at 8/7c as part of the network’s Love of a Lifetime November romance movie slate, He Wasn’t Man Enough, stars Braxton as bestselling author Mel Montgomery, whose world unravels when she discovers her boyfriend Richard (Thomas Cadrot) has been deceiving her. When Mel learns Richard is now engaged to her estranged college friend Monica (Atkins), the two women, with the help of Mel’s loyal best friend Candy (Brown), set aside old wounds to stand together. What begins as betrayal becomes a story of resilience and solidarity—proving Richard picked the wrong trio to mess with. Because in the end, it was never about the man who failed them, but the women who chose each other.  Always and without question… sisters over misters.

#ToniBraxtonHeWasntManEnough

snippet.title: "Wuthering Heights" | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Inspired by the greatest love story of all time. “Wuthering Heights” only in theaters this Valentine’s Day. #WutheringHeightsMovie

Pre-order Charli xcx's new album "Wuthering Heights": https://wutheringheights.charlixcx.com/

From Warner Bros. Pictures and Academy Award and BAFTA-winning filmmaker Emerald Fennell comes “WUTHERING HEIGHTS,” starring Academy Award and BAFTA nominee Margot Robbie opposite BAFTA nominee Jacob Elordi.

A bold and original imagining of one of the greatest love stories of all time, Emerald Fennell’s “WUTHERING HEIGHTS” stars Margot Robbie as Cathy and Jacob Elordi as Heathcliff, whose forbidden passion for one another turns from romantic to intoxicating in an epic tale of lust, love and madness.

The film also stars alongside Oscar nominee Hong Chau, Shazad Latif, Alison Oliver, BAFTA winner Martin Clunes and Ewan Mitchell.

Fennell directs from her own screenplay, and produces alongside Oscar nominee and BAFTA award winner Josey McNamara and Robbie. Oscar nominee Tom Ackerley and Sara Desmond are executive producing.

Behind the scenes, Fennell worked with such frequent collaborators as Oscar- and BAFTA-winning director of photography Linus Sandgren, Oscar- and BAFTA-nominated production designer Suzie Davies, BAFTA-nominated editor Victoria Boydell, award-winning casting director Kharmel Cochrane and BAFTA-nominated composer Anthony Willis. Oscar and BAFTA winner Jacqueline Durran designed the costumes. Original songs by Charli XCX.

Warner Bros. Pictures and MRC Present A Lie Still & LuckyChap Entertainment Production, a film by Emerald Fennell, “WUTHERING HEIGHTS.” Distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures, the film will be in theaters nationwide on February 13, 2026, and internationally beginning 11 February.

snippet.title: STRANGER THINGS 5: VOLUME 1 | FINAL TRAILER (2025) | Netflix
snippet.description:
#Netflix #StrangerThings #StrangerThings5

🎥 Attention viewers! (ITS FAN MADE)
The final battle for Hawkins begins.
Stranger Things Season 5 marks the epic conclusion to Netflix’s biggest supernatural saga, as Eleven, Mike, Will, Dustin, Lucas, Max, Nancy, Steve, Robin, Jonathan, Joyce, and Hopper face the darkness of the Upside Down one last time. With Vecna rising stronger than ever, old wounds return, alliances are tested, and the fate of the world hangs in the balance.
This is the beginning of the end.

The inspiration behind this video:
The final chapter begins. The Stranger Things Season 5 Trailer offers a dramatic and emotional look at the closing story of Hawkins, setting the stage for the ultimate showdown between Eleven and Vecna. As the Stranger Things Season 5 narrative unfolds, the town faces its darkest hour yet. Featuring powerful moments with Millie Bobby Brown, Finn Wolfhard, Noah Schnapp, Caleb McLaughlin, Sadie Sink, Gaten Matarazzo, and the entire ensemble, this trailer hints at the end of an era for Netflix’s most iconic series.

This new look continues the momentum built by the Stranger Things 5 Final Season Trailer 2 and the Stranger Things 5 Official Teaser, expanding the mystery surrounding the Upside Down and the fate of Hawkins. Characters like Maya Hawke, Joe Keery, Natalia Dyer, Charlie Heaton, Cara Buono, Winona Ryder, David Harbour, and Jamie Campbell Bower (Vecna) return with emotional weight and renewed urgency. With Chief Hopper, Eleven, Mike Wheeler, Dustin, Lucas, Max, Jonathan Byers, Joyce Byers, Will Byers, and Steve Harrington all pushed to their limits, the final season promises high stakes and unforgettable moments.

As Netflix prepares to close this chapter, fans can expect cinematic storytelling, intense character arcs, and a battle unlike anything Stranger Things has delivered before. This trailer compiles the energy and style viewers love from creators like Rotten Tomatoes TV, Teaser PRO, FilmSpot Trailer, MovieGasm, KinoCheck, EmergencyAwesome, and IGN TV Trailer, making it a must-watch for anyone following the series. The final fight for Hawkins has officially begun.
